    <h2> MY RESEARCH </h2>
    <p class="black"> I am interested in the mental world of primates â€“ the unique cognitive functioning that exists in humans and to some extant, in non-human primates. I am interested in abstract thought and processes like working memory that rely on mental representations that are separable from sensory and motor signals.
I am also interested in how cognitive function is impacted by stress and mental illness.
 </p>
<p class="black"> My research approach focuses on neuron population coding in the prefrontal cortex in non-human primates. I have used a combination of extracellular recordings, pharmacology, and machine learning to explore working memory representations in naturalistic conditions utilizing virtual reality technology. 
</p>


